## 10. Cloud Architecture

### Vercel (Frontend)

- **What:** CDN + serverless runtime for Next.js
- **Where code runs:** Server Components and API routes run on Vercel's serverless functions (Node.js). Middleware runs on Edge Runtime (V8 isolates, no Node.js APIs).
- **Domain:** `atrosha.bond` with automatic HTTPS
- **Cold start:** Edge functions start in ~0ms. Serverless functions in ~50–200ms (first request after idle). Subsequent requests: warm.

### Render (Backend)

- **What:** PaaS — runs Docker containers with managed networking
- **Proxy:** Always-on web service (not serverless), so no cold start when agents call it
- **Semantic Engine:** Always-on worker service, private network only
- **Redis:** Managed Redis instance, internal IP only (no public exposure)

### Supabase (Database + Auth)

- **What:** Managed PostgreSQL + auth service + storage + edge functions
- **Auth:** Runs as a sidecar service alongside PostgreSQL. Issues JWTs signed with Supabase's private key.
- **RLS (Row Level Security):** PostgreSQL policies that ensure users can only see their org's data
- **Location:** Supabase projects run in one AWS region (you pick). Not globally distributed.

### Why This Split?

| Concern | Service | Reason |
|---------|---------|--------|
| User-facing website | Vercel | Global CDN, Next.js integration, zero-config SSL |
| Always-on API proxy | Render | Persistent containers, no cold start, internal networking |
| Database + Auth | Supabase | Managed PostgreSQL with auth batteries included |
| Audit analytics | ClickHouse | Columnar, append-only, fast analytics |
| Operational state | Redis | Sub-millisecond reads, atomic Lua scripts |

### Inter-Service Communication

```
Vercel (edge) ──HTTPS──► Supabase Auth API
Vercel (server fn) ──HTTPS──► Supabase DB (PostgREST API)
Render Proxy ──internal──► Render Redis (no TLS, private network)
Render Proxy ──internal──► Render Semantic Engine (no TLS, private network)
Render Proxy ──HTTPS──► External APIs (Stripe, Coinbase, etc.)
Stripe ──HTTPS──► Vercel /api/billing/webhook
```

